        <property propertyId="67f102e2-9cb6-4d20-aa16-bf74d8a03326" amount="1.0" isDefiningValue="false" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7">
          <name xml:lang="en">wet mass</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. According to the European Chemical Agency, the consumption of Sodium nitrate for the year of 2016 is estimated to be 550000000 kg. The aforementioned value is the average of the range given in the literature. According to the European Chemical Industry Council (Cefic, 2016a), the total sales of chemicals of the European Union in 2016 amounted to 519 billion euros. Chemical imports were valued at 91 billion euros for the first 11 months of 2016. Based on this, the value for the total imports for the year 2016 was extrapolated, yielding a value of 99.3 billion euros. Furthermore, Cefic (2016b) reports a trade surplus (exports-imports) of 46.4 billion euros (once again extrapolated for the whole year using the value of 42 billion euros for the first 11 months of 2016). Considering all the aforementioned information, the total chemical consumption in the EU is calculated to be 472.6 billion euros (total sales-exports+imports). It is therefore calculated that production is 110% of consumption. This value is used to scale the information on chemical consumption to production. The European production volume is therefore 605000000 kg.

References:
European Chemical Agency, Brief profile of Sodium nitrate, Accessible at: https://echa.europa.eu/brief-profile/-/briefprofile/100.028.944
Cefic 2016a. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
Cefic 2016b. 2016: EU chemicals output posts positive growth for third year running. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Documents/RESOURCES/Chemical%20Trends%20Report/March-2017-Cefic-Chemicals-Trends-Report.pdf
</productionVolumeComment>
